                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d533">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/680.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mexican Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-02-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 2, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 407.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to the embassy’s note of the 3d ultimo,
                    wherein this Department was informed that Abraham González, Cástulo Herrera and
                    P. J. Lomelí were engaged in seditious acts at El Paso, Tex., and request was
                    made that this Government take action against them for violating the neutrality
                    laws of the United States, I have now <pb facs="0483" n="401" xml:id="pg_401"/>
                    the honor to inform you of the receipt of a letter dated the 27th ultimo from
                    the Acting Attorney General, stating that a copy of the embassy’s note had been
                    forwarded to the United States attorney for the western district of Texas, with
                    instructions to investigate the matter and institute criminal proceedings
                    against these men, if it is found that they have violated the neutrality laws of
                    the United States.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
